		without wanting to explain the minutia of how it would be applied within a specific,
		contemporary real - world context.There is an excellent article on this at < a href = \"http://io9.gizmodo.com/5932802/the-philosophical-roots-of-science-fiction\">Gizmodo</a> which is linked in the show notes. Many people have suggested that Plato’s allegory of the cave is the prototype of a science fiction story, since it speculates about an unseen other world, which people have only seen the shadows of. The modern version of this story is The Matrix.
